---
title: Hoisin-Sesame Roasted Veggie Bowls with Ginger Rice & Spicy Soy Mayo
description: We’re big fans of the ubiquitous “Buddha bowl,” but we have to admit: this one’s extra special. It’s a one-bowl veggie feast that’s positively bursting with flavor. The base is a heap of fluffy rice simmered with scallions and ginger. On top, there’s hoisin-and-sesame-glazed sweet potatoes and mushrooms, roasted bell pepper, spicy soy mayo, and a scattering of sesame seeds and scallion greens. One bite will have you feeling totally zen.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hoisin-sesame-roasted-veggie-bowls-45ee9fe5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-sesame-roasted-veggie-bowls-5eb9bbb1470e7a2f041a8f28-c4cbd5dc.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 101 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1300 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-sesame-roasted-veggie-bowls-5eb9bbb1470e7a2f041a8f28
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Dice @sweet potatoes{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @cremini mushrooms{8%ounce}. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and 1 TBSP ginger (2 TBSP for 4); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Roast on top rack until just tender, ~{15%minutes} (they'll finish cooking in step 5).

> For 4 servings, use 2 sheets; roast sweet potatoes and mushrooms on top rack and bell peppers on middle rack.

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and as much @?sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

> TIP: Start with half the sriracha, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Using a #spatula{}, toss sweet potato and mushrooms with remaining hoisin and half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for serving). Return to oven until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a fork and season with @salt{}; divide between #bowls{}. Arrange sweet potato, mushrooms, and bell pepper on top in their own sections. Drizzle everything with as much spicy soy mayo as you like. Top with scallion greens and remaining sesame seeds. Serve.